('Barbell Bent-Over Row (Pendlay Style)',
 'back', array['biceps','rear_deltoid','erectors'], array['back','biceps','erectors'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Pendlay row: bar starts on the floor each rep (strict). Stand over bar, hip-hinge to near-parallel torso, grip just outside shoulder-width, overhand grip. Row explosively from the floor to the lower chest/upper abdomen, then return the bar to the floor completely. Back remains parallel throughout. This is a power movement — the goal is explosive hip and back drive, not a slow controlled row. Teaches lat recruitment from a dead start. Excellent for strength and thickness development.',
 'Raising the torso during the pull (not a row — a deadlift); not returning bar to floor each rep; gripping too wide; not using leg drive to support the back angle; wrist curling instead of elbow driving.',
 'back_hypertrophy', array['Torso stays parallel: this is non-negotiable','Bar to chest: lower chest or navel, not higher','Back to floor each rep: this is the Pendlay distinction','Explosive: generate power, do not slow-grind this movement'],
 array['Pendlay row with bands for accommodating resistance','Barbell row with pause at top','Heavy Pendlay row with belt for maximum loading'],
 array['Dumbbell bent-over row','Chest-supported row (less lower back)','Cable row seated'],
 array['bodybuilding','back','pendlay_row','barbell','power','thickness','bent_over'], array['lower_back_disc','lower_back_pain'],
