('Wide-Grip Pullup Weighted',
 'back', array['biceps','rear_deltoid'], array['back','biceps'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['pullup_bar','weight_belt','dumbbell'], 'advanced', true,
 'Attach weight via a dip belt or hold a dumbbell between feet. Grip the bar wider than shoulder-width with an overhand grip (pronated). Start from a dead hang — full shoulder extension. Pull up by driving the elbows down and back, not by pulling with the arms. Bring the upper chest to the bar. Control the descent back to full hang. Wide grip increases lat stretch at the bottom and emphasizes the outer lat sweep. Do not use kipping or momentum.',
 'Not reaching a full dead hang between reps; pulling with the arms instead of the lats; not bringing the chest to the bar; kipping on a weighted pullup; using a supinated grip (changes to chinup).',
 'back_hypertrophy', array['Dead hang: full shoulder extension every rep','Elbows drive down: not pulling with biceps','Chest to bar: get to the top fully','Wide is wider: go 6 inches outside shoulder, not just at shoulder'],
 array['Extreme wide-grip pullup','Weighted pullup with pause at top','One-arm pullup progression'],
 array['Bodyweight pullup','Band-assisted pullup','Lat pulldown (machine assistance)'],
