('Competition Posing Practice – Full Routine',
 'core', array['chest','back','shoulder','quadriceps'], array['core','chest','back','shoulder','quadriceps'],
 'functional', 'other', array['bodyweight'], 'advanced', false,
 'Competition posing is a trained skill requiring as much practice as lifting. Full routine: (1) Mandatory poses: front double bicep, front lat spread, side chest, back double bicep, back lat spread, side tricep, most muscular. (2) Free posing: 60-90 second music routine. Practice: 15-20 minutes daily for 12+ weeks pre-competition. Practice in front of a large mirror or with a coach. Video every practice session. Hold each mandatory pose 30-60 seconds for muscular conditioning. Transitions between poses are judged — smooth is important.',
 'Not practicing posing daily (posing muscles need conditioning — shaking within 10 seconds means underprepared); poor transitions between poses; incorrect mandatory pose form (each federation has specific standards); neglecting the back poses (most competitors are weakest here).',
 'competition_prep', array['Daily practice: 15-20 minutes every day — posing is cardio','Video yourself: you cannot see your own back without video','Hold 30 seconds each pose: build posing muscle conditioning','Hire a posing coach: this is an investment that pays in placings'],
